{"questionId":"25760799","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A meteorologist models the height of a hot air balloon launched from the ground. The model&nbsp;assumes the balloon travels vertically upwards and travels <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>450</mn></math> metres in the first minute.</p>\n<p>Due to the decrease in temperature as the balloon rises, the balloon will continually slow down.&nbsp;The model suggests that each minute the balloon will travel only <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>82</mn><mo>%</mo></math> of the distance travelled&nbsp;in the previous minute.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find how high the balloon will travel in the first <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn></math> minutes after it is launched.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognition of geometric sequence <em>eg</em>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>82</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mn>10</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>450</mn><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>82</mn><mn>10</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>82</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2160</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>2156</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>37</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br></strong></em><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25760799","referenceCode":"21M.1.AHL.TZ2.7a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find how high the balloon will travel in the first 10 minutes after it is launched.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.3—Geometric sequences and series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.11—Sum of infinite geometric sequences"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}